body:
While modeling an asynchronous FIFO according to "Simulation and Synthesis Techniques for Asynchronous FIFO Design with Asynchronous Pointer Comparisons" by Clifford E. Cummings and Peter Alfke SNUG 2002, I had to describe a DFF with async CLR and PRE, like this:

```
module ff_clr_pre
  (
   input  clk,
   input  clr,
   input  pre,
   input  d,
   output reg q);

 always @(posedge clk or posedge clr or posedge pre) 
 begin : do_ff
  if (clr)
     q <= 1'b0;
  else if (pre)
     q <= 1'b1;
  else
     q <= d;
 end // d0_ff
 endmodule // ff_clr_pre
```
When I run:

> yoysys  -q -p "synth_ice40 -blif test.blif" test.v

I get a warning about complex reset:

> Warning: Complex async reset for dff `\q'.

And the BLIF output contains an unmaped $\_DFFSR_PPP\_
I don't know how to add mapping rules. One solution to this problem is to use 2 flip-flops. The first flip-flop implements the async preset and the normal D/Q behavior. The second flip-flop is used to generate the async clear. This flip-flop has D tied to Vcc and has CLR. The modeled output is the and between both FFs:

```
module DFF_ASR
  (
   input  d_i,
   output q_o,
   input  clk_i,
   input  clr_i,
   input  pre_i);
// Simpler FF, only preset
reg q;
always @(posedge clk_i or posedge pre_i)
begin : do_ff
  if (pre_i)
     q <= 1'b1;
  else
     q <= d_i;
end // do_ff
// Another FF for clear
reg q_clr;
always @(posedge clk_i or posedge clr_i)
begin : do_clr
  if (clr_i)
     q_clr <= 1'b0;
  else
     q_clr <= 1'b1;
end // do_clr
// Output is conditioned by the clear FF
assign q_o=q & q_clr;
endmodule // DFF_ASR
```
The yosys version I'm using is:

Yosys 0.7+207 (git sha1 ea805af6, gcc 6.3.0-18 -O2 -fdebug-prefix-map=/home/salvador/0Data/IceStorm/Yosys/Debian-git/yosys=. -fstack-p
rotector-strong -fPIC -Os)

